<HEAD>Four Killed In Riot Caused By Hit-and-Run Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hit-and-run bus accident touched off a
clash between police and people armed with broken bottles and
stones, and four people were shot to death and five injured,
authorities said Sunday.
   Police said the riot occurred Friday night when a bus driver
trying to escape a traffic policeman ran down and killed a commuter.
   Youths in the area of central Lagos began attacking police and
government vehicles, injuring five policemen, one of them
critically, police said.
   Riot police sent to the scene were greeted by rocks and bottles
thrown from behind a barracade erected by the rioters, police said.
   Authorities fired tear gas and pistols to break up the riot.
Police said four people died from bullet wounds.
   Last month a policeman was sentenced to death for killing two men
involved in a traffic dispute. That traffic accident caused riots
that left eight people dead.
</TEXT>
