<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Philippines-Cult     03-05 0148</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Philippines-Cult,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rumors of Satanic Cult Stir Fears</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ZAMBOANGA CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rumors that a devil-worshiping
cult is kidnapping women and children has spread fear in this city,
prompting parents to keep children home at night and setting off a
police inquiry.
   Police Capt. Nonito Gader dismissed the reported cult as a hoax
perpetrated by ``drug addicts or pranksters.'' He said surveillance
of several neighborhoods in Zamboanga failed to turn up evidence of
devil worship.
   The rumors surfaced after leaflets describing a cult turned up in
schools, markets and even government offices in this southern city
of 500,000 people. The leaflets, allegedly from the United Satanic
Evil Design, include a list of the cult's holy days as well as
secret signs to identify members.
   Unconfirmed word spread, however, that the cult is kidnapping
women and children for rituals.
   Mystical religious cults are widespread in the Philippines.
</TEXT>
