<HEAD>Ivanchuk Wins International Tournament</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LINARES, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vasily Ivanchuk of the Soviet Union won the
international City of Linares chess tournament after drawing with
Lajos Portisch of Hungary in the 11th and last round.
   The 20-year-old Soviet ended the tournament unbeaten Saturday
with a total of 7.5 points. He earned $6,521.
   Former world champion Anatoli Karpov, also of the Soviet Union,
drew with Jan Timman, of the Netherlands, and was second in the
final standings with seven points. He won $4,348.
   Other results in the last round were:
   Nigel Short, Britain, defeated Johan Hjartarson of Iceland. Short
finished at 5.5 and Hjartarson with three points.
   Andrei Sokolov, Soviet Union at 3.5, drew with Alexander
Beliavsky, also of the Soviet Union, who had 4.5.
