<FIRST>r i AM-Italy-Avalanche     03-05 0151</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Italy-Avalanche,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Killed In Avalanche</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AOSTA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four Austrian tourists were swept away by an
avalanche as they were skiing Sunday in northern Italy, and one of
them was killed, civil defense officials said.
   Two skiiers managed to free themselves from the snow and another
was rescued by Alpine guides who rushed to the scene in the Aosta
Valley in a helicopter, the officials said.
   The Italian news agency ANSA identified the dead man as Karl
Schmeikal, 50, of Salzburg, Austria. He was skiing with his wife
Hilde and two friends when the avalanche occurred near La Thuile, at
an altitude of about 6,000 feet, ANSA said.
   Mrs. Schmeikal and the two other members of the group trapped in
the avalanche were not injured, civil defense officials said.
   Italian authorities have warned that avalanches may occur because
of the warm, sunny weather that followed recent heavy snowfalls.
</TEXT>
