<HEAD>Rock Musician's Son Dies at University</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Note contents</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eli D. Danko, the 18-year-old son of rock
musician Rick Danko, choked to death on his own vomit after a
college party, the Albany County coroner's office said Sunday.
   Danko's body was found in his dormitory room at the State
University of New York at Albany when a fellow student went to wake
him for classes Friday, said Barbara Cavanaugh, a secretary to the
coroner.
   Students said Danko, a freshman, had been at a campus party the
night before and was ``quite drunk'' when he left around 2 a.m.
Friday, Cavanaugh said. She said the results of laboratory tests on
Danko's level of intoxication had not come back yet.
   Rick Danko, who lives in Bearsville between Albany and New York
City, was a member of the rock group The Band and now tours as a
solo act.
   His son was born in Rhinebeck, across the Hudson River.
   Eli Danko is also survived his mother, Grace Seldner of San
Rafael, Calif., his stepmother, Elizabeth, and two stepbrothers and
a sister.
